This paper deals with type theory, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the structure of typing judgments, which is relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents a new approach to type theory, which could be of interest to the machine learning community (cs.LG) as it involves the use of infinite contexts.
